title: For Sale:  Savage A17 with 4-12-40 Prostaff Scope
postcontent: Now here is a deal. A like new (I have about 75 rounds through the gun) semi-auto .17HMR Savage A17 with bright new Nikon Prostaff Rimfire 4-12x40 BDC reticle scope ($120 retail) and two EXTRA 10 shot clip($20 each retail) . Bought everything new for about $560. Had issues with the first one I bought and Savage sent me a new one. Add some issues with feeding at first but found that these need to be broken in. The Prostaff scope is pretty nice glass for a rimfire, some issues with eye relief on 12x but once you figure it out it is right on. I have the rig dialed in at 100yrds and on a good bench and rest with a heavy rear bag had a 6 shot group (two consecutive 3 shot groups) that were all on the 1" target. One group was just over 5/8" and the best was 5/16'. I was blown away (as my neighbor was) when we checked the group, that an inexpensive rimfire could be so accurate. (Now it was a perfect day for shooting a .17 cool, no wind and a great stand/rest) I had my doubts about these rifles but am a believer now. IT's in almost like new, may be a few bumps from shooting from a bench but NOTHING is wrong with it. Bought the gun on a whim but decided to step up to a new 222. I had a Ruger Model 77 in 17HMR for fox hunting in Alaska and, I can't believe I'm saying this, but this A17 is dang close as accurate. The cheapest one of these I can find on Gunbroker, CheaperThanDirt, etc is $395 plus shipping. So at $399 with scope and 2 extra mags, this is a good deal so please don't try and low ball. Can't/won't go any lower. If you are a "horse-trader" tell your wife I was asking $510 and you talked me down $100.I'll take $399 plus $35 shipping for total of $445 and I'll send to your FFL. That is like buying a rifle retail and get a scope and Two Extra clips FOR FREE.If picked up locally have 550 rounds of CCI A17 ammo and 50 rounds of hollow points (600 rounds total) I  will give you for $95 ($149 retail). Can do PayPal and/or Money order. Paypal gets it to you quicker.

title: For Sale:  Emergency Preparedness SAM Chest Seal with Valve NSN# 6510-01-606-7097
postcontent: Click here to purchaseWHAT IS THE SAM® CHEST SEAL  The SAM® Chest Seal is a new occlusive dressing designed for treating open chest wounds (also known as a sucking chest wound), a life-threatening situation that could lead to tension pneumothorax. This is the second leading cause of preventable death on the battlefield.  WHY THE SAM® CHEST SEAL  Key features of the SAM® Chest Seal include its strong adhesive and its flexible construction which allows conformability over the wound. The adhesive properties have been tested to simulate various environments including adhesion to hair, sweat, blood, in the presence of sand, submersion in water, and during extended wear. The chest seal also adheres under extreme heat and cold.  Another key advantage of the strong adhesion is its ability to reseal, making it ideal for venting the wound. The SAM® Chest Seal addresses other military needs including a larger dressing area, and by including a highly and rapidly absorbent 5" x 9" pad for cleaning the wound area before application.  ONE-WAY VALVE OPTION  This version features a one-way valve, when its cap is removed. The one-way valve provides for low resistance flow of air out of the chest cavity while preventing ingress. The valve is also designed to prevent blockage internally. With the cap in place, the dressing is occlusive.
